Description: Fragment of oval handle of a pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay fine mid red-brown; hard fired. Rectangular stamp with rounded top.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 188a, 21. As Pridik, Catalogue of stamps ..... Hermitage, pl. 16, 14.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1683)
